# Subservices — {SERVICE_NAME}

> Master registry of subservices. Compile reads this to route facts; skills pages read this to find backing assets.
> **Adding a new subservice or authority:** add an entry below + run `register-subservice.sh` to create matching folders.

## Registered Subservices

<!-- Example single-authority subservice -->

### {subservice-slug}

- **authority_mode:** `single` (flat category structure, no authority nesting)
- **Description:** {one-line description}
- **Scope:** {what this subservice covers}
- **Wiki paths:**
  - Skills: `skills/{subservice-slug}/{regulations,methodology,tools,schemes}/`
  - Candidates: `candidate/{subservice-slug}/{regulations,methodology,tools,schemes}/`
  - Projects: `projects/{subservice-slug}/`
- **Assets path:** `assets/{AssetsFolder}/`
- **Deliverables:** {list of output files}

<!-- Example multi-authority subservice -->

### {subservice-slug-multi}

- **authority_mode:** `multi` (authority folder sits between subservice and category)
- **Description:** {one-line description}
- **Scope:** {what this subservice covers}
- **Planning authorities used:**
  - **{auth-slug-1}** ({AuthorityName1}) — assets: `assets/{path}/`
    - Wiki skills: `skills/{subservice}/{auth-slug-1}/{cats}/`
    - Candidates: `candidate/{subservice}/{auth-slug-1}/{cats}/`
  - **{auth-slug-2}** ({AuthorityName2}) — assets: `assets/{path}/`
    - Wiki skills: `skills/{subservice}/{auth-slug-2}/{cats}/`
    - Candidates: `candidate/{subservice}/{auth-slug-2}/{cats}/`
  - **shared** — cross-authority facts (billing, compliance, reporting)

## Notes

- `single` mode = one authority or regulator covers all work; no authority folder.
- `multi` mode = multiple authorities; nest their folder between subservice and category.
- `shared/` is always available under multi-auth for cross-authority facts.
- Categories inside each subservice/authority: `regulations`, `methodology`, `tools`, `schemes`.
